1.title: Introduction
1.plot: Shots of the exterior of a car are shown as someone drives, and text overlays this footage explaining the premise of the story from Jay's point of view.

2.title: Entry #1
2.plot: J has started going through Alex's Marble Hornets video tapes and is posting various findings. This one reveals something unusual in the footage.

3.title: Entry #2
3.plot: In another Marble Hornets tape that J has watched, this one involves Alex driving and describing something very strange that happened when he took his dog for a walk earlier.

4.title: Entry #3
4.plot: This entry includes clips from several different tapes that show Alex filming himself doing various tasks in his home and in other places. Jay notes that Alex seemingly "wanted to have a camera on himself at all times".

5.title: Entry #4
5.plot: This tape shows Alex running from the mysterious figure from Entry #1 in a playground.

6.title: Entry #5
6.plot: Jay found a tape which includes Alex and Jay location scouting for the film Marble hornets. The audio is severely distorted. We see a gazebo, and also a red tower in the distance.

7.title: Entry #6
7.plot: Jay finds another tape that could be a possible continuation from Entry #1.

8.title: Entry #7
8.plot: During the filming of a scene of Marble Hornets, Alex sees his stalker.

9.title: Entry #8
9.plot: Jay finds a tape where Alex is drawing pictures of the figure, when the audio cuts out and he seems to panic.

10.title: Entry #9
10.plot: More raw footage from Marble Hornets reveals that Alex is constantly on edge during filming, and Jay presumes that the person following him is the source of the anger.

11.title: Regards
11.plot: The first totheark video, with a message that reads "LOOK CLOSELY."

12.title: Entry #10
12.plot: Alex runs through the woods, while being chased by his mysterious stalker.

13.title: Operator
13.plot: The second totheark video, with a message that reads "Lakes In Stillnesss Will Take Every life of the Night." The capital letters spell out "LISTEN."

14.title: Entry #11
14.plot: Alex is sleeping when he gets up and checks downstairs. As he checks, he misses something important: His stalker looking in at him.

15.title: Deluge
15.plot: Totheark video which contains the words "Watching You" and a reversed, slowed down woman's voice calling out for Alex.

16.title: Entry #12
16.plot: Another scene for Marble Hornets is filmed, but with some visual and audio distortion, and later an appearance by Alex's stalker.

17.title: Impurity
17.plot: Totheark video with a thunderstorm and a message that reads: "THERE WAS M0RE."

18.title: Entry #13
18.plot: Alex and Jay are out shooting. When Jay goes back to the car for more tapes, Alex goes exploring, and finds a strange symbol and his stalker.

19.title: Exit
19.plot: A totheark video shows Jay walking to his car (referenced in Entry #13), and a hidden message that asks "WHEREIS THE ARK".

20.title: Entry #14
20.plot: The Operator enters Alex's room, but seems to disappear when the lights turn on. Alex then appears with blood trickling down his face. Jay decides it's time to find out where Alex is.

21.title: Program
21.plot: A shot of a house with rain, a moving S in the left corner, a bunch of zeroes, and the words "BLE ED MO RE" appear in the latest totheark video.

22.title: Entry #15 - Interview with Tim
22.plot: Jay tracks down Tim, a former cast member from Marble Hornets, and talks to him about the film under the pretense of starting the film up again.

23.title: Advocate
23.plot: Distorted footage of Brian is used, while "TICK TOCK" appears on the screen and a countdown in binary is shown.

24.title: Entry #16
24.plot: Jay enters the house that Brian was last known to be at, and starts experiencing some strange phenomena as he explores.

25.title: Addition
25.plot: Totheark video reveals that the person behind this account was in the house with Jay in the previous entry.

26.title: Entry #17
26.plot: Jay uncovers footage from the filming of Marble Hornets, including the Operator in the trees and things he doesn't remember happening.

27.title: Signal
27.plot: Totheark video that features a man's voice, creepy imagery, and the words "come back."

28.title: Entry #18
28.plot: Jay returns to the house and finds a masked man. He later escapes, but wakes up the next day with no memory of the events after and the same audio distortion at the end of the video.

29.title: Messages
29.plot: Totheark video with Pearl Harbor footage, an ominous warning, and a photo of Tim.

30.title: Entry #19
30.plot: Jay reveals that he has been filming himself like Alex, and finds out that the masked person from the previous entry knows where he lives.

31.title: Return
31.plot: A shot of Jay, the Operator and the words "FOU ND YOU" and "forever" appear in the latest totheark video.

32.title: Entry #19.5
32.plot: Jay runs through the items he found in the sixteenth entry, and expresses the fact that the trail might have gone cold.

33.title: Entry #20
33.plot: Jay shows us the last tape, with more things he cannot remember. He then decides to go to the red tower from Entry #5.

34.title: Version
34.plot: An inverted image of the red tower, with some fast-moving words and the sentence: "Waiting for you."

35.title: Entry #21
35.plot: Jay goes to the red tower and finds a tape.

36.title: Entry #22
36.plot: The tape found by Jay in the previous entry is shown.

37.title: Attention
37.plot: A totheark video with old footage and the words "Wake up."

38.title: Admission
38.plot: Someone is inside a house, and the sentence "There are doors unopened" appears in this totheark video.

39.title: Entry #23
39.plot: Jay returns to the house one last time and encounters the masked man again. As he pursues him, he finds out that things are not what they seem.

40.title: Warning
40.plot: The final totheark video of Season One has quotes from the previous videos repeated along with footage of the Masked Man.

41.title: Entry #24
41.plot: Jay has set up surveillance cameras around his house, and they catch him somehow leaving his house (which is impossible due to blocked exits), and then returning.

42.title: Entry ######
42.plot: The Marble Hornets channel is hacked by totheark.

43.title: Entry #25
43.plot: Jay has moved to a hotel for the time being, and gets a call to turn on the news to find that his apartment has been set on fire.

44.title: Entry #26
44.plot: In the first season finale, Jay plans to move away and get away from Marble Hornets, before a tape shows up at his door proving that Alex is alive.

1.title: Entry #27
1.plot: In the second season premiere, Jay wakes up in a hotel room seven months after the last entry, with no memory of those months. He decides that he's going to lay low, and get to the bottom of this.

2.title: Entry #28
2.plot: Jay searches his hotel room for clues, and meets a girl named Jessica who may be part of the mystery.

3.title: Entry #29
3.plot: Jay finds a video hidden on his hard drive entitled "noentry" and discovers that it includes a bloody rock and The Operator.

4.title: Entry #30
4.plot: Jay meets Jessica again, and notices some weird camera activity when she's around. That night, he hears weird noises coming from her room, and tries to confront her, to no avail.

5.title: Entry #31
5.plot: Jay goes looking for the place shown in Entry #29, but finds a mysterious man following him. Later, he talks to Jessica again, where she reveals she may have been affected by The Operator.

6.title: Entry #32
6.plot: Jay gets confronted by Jessica, who is also having memory loss. The two decide to meet in her room, while Jay uploads the entry in case something happens.

7.title: Entry #33
7.plot: Jay goes back to Jessica's room, but finds her missing and the combination to the safe in his room. After grabbing things from the safe, the Masked Man appears.

8.title: Entry #34
8.plot: Jay begins going through the tapes, starting with one from April 21st, which shows him going to the return address of the package he was sent.

9.title: Fragments
9.plot: Totheark returns with a video of torn-up pictures of Alex, and the words "you are broken" and "you cannot be fixed."

10.title: Entry #35
10.plot: Jay goes back to the building, with Alex, and the two meet Tim, who turns out to be someone they know.

11.title: Broadcast
11.plot: Totheark video which has a person narrating in a very distorted audio format.

12.title: Entry #36
12.plot: Jay finds corrupted footage at the end of the tape from the last entry, and finds out that Alex was the one who sent the package to him.

13.title: Sidetone
13.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

14.title: Entry #37
14.plot: The channel is hacked again, and we see birthday footage of Alex, with some strange things put into the tape.

15.title: Entry #38
15.plot: Jay finds an unlabeled tape that has him and Alex walking through the woods, while Alex tells a story about those woods. Jay is uneasy about how Alex acts.

16.title: Entry #39
16.plot: Jay gets a call from Alex about a week after the last time they met, and Alex says to meet him at Rosswood Park. Later that night, outside Jay's window, a man is seen looking in at him.

17.title: Forecast
17.plot: A totheark video that shows he was the one outside Jay's car, and that something sinister is going on.

18.title: Entry #40
18.plot: The day after Jay gets the call, he goes to Rosswood Park and can't find Alex. As he walks around, he encounters The Operator.

19.title: Intermission
19.plot: A totheark video that shows images implying the Masked Man was in the forest with Alex, and the message, "Did you see me? I saw you."

20.title: Entry #41
20.plot: After 15 minutes of silence on the tape from Entry #40, the camera is picked up and taken back to Jay's car, where it's revealed that a masked person was the one who brought it back.

21.title: Indicator
21.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

22.title: Entry #42
22.plot: Alex makes it to the park and finds Jay hysterical, after being in contact with The Operator. Jay later finds his camera in his car, with no idea of how it got there.

23.title: Memories
23.plot: Totheark video which includes the ominous message: "So much more than time has been taken."

24.title: Entry #43
24.plot: Alex and Jay go back to Amy's house, looking for Amy, but find nothing. Later, Alex goes to the woods alone and meets the Operator.

25.title: Inquiry
25.plot: Another totheark video, posing some questions about who he is and who you are.

26.title: Entry #44
26.plot: Alex is alone at home when he starts coughing, drawing pictures involving the Operator symbol, and seeing the Operator himself.

27.title: Entry #45
27.plot: Alex is at home, when he suddenly chases after a masked man outside. The masked man overcomes him, when it's revealed that two of them exist.

28.title: Entry #46
28.plot: Jay follows Alex to his house and sneaks inside, finding a tape before Alex catches him. The Operator appears, and Jay escapes, not without taking both the tape and a key.

29.title: Classified
29.plot: Totheark video which asks the question: "Do you know what he did?"

30.title: Entry #47
30.plot: Alex confronts Jay about the break-in, which leads to Jay and Alex splitting up, but not before Jay gets Jessica's phone number. He calls Jessica, who tells him that Alex has apparently found Amy.

31.title: Entry #48
31.plot: Jay starts following Alex, and eventually discovers that he's been going into the woods, and to the same tunnel from Entry #29. He decides to look at Alex's footage to get a clearer idea of what's going on.

32.title: Sidenote
32.plot: Totheark video that tells the viewer to "be silent", and that "this is the best part".

33.title: Entry #49
33.plot: Alex goes to the tunnel as shown in Entry #48. The man in the white shirt follows him and when Alex sees, he kills him. The Operator takes the body. Alex tells Jay to meet him at Rosswood Park.

34.title: Extraction
34.plot: Totheark video connecting Tim and the Masked Man. "How much do you hate? It is not enough."

35.title: Entry #50
35.plot: Jay and Alex go to Rosswood Park, but end up with nothing. Jay sees the Masked Man. He gives chase but is unsuccessful. The next day, Jay sneaks into Alex's apartment again and grabs the tape that he didn't grab the last time.

36.title: Entry #51
36.plot: The tape that Jay stole ends up being more footage from Marble Hornets. The truth about what happened to Brian comes to light.

37.title: Entry #52
37.plot: In the second season finale, Jay finally pieces together the last days of his 7-month gap.

imdb.plot outline: When a film student decides to look through the tapes of a canceled project his friend Alex had directed, and he had participated in, he discovers that his friends have been stalked by a paranormal entity known as the Operator and has now gotten himself involved in a mystery that goes beyond anything he can understand.
imdb.title: Marble Hornets
plot: When film student Jay gets some tapes from his friend Alex containing footage of a cancelled film project called _Marble Hornets_ (qv), he is followed by an entity called The Operator and finds out the secrets behind the tapes.

When a film student decides to look through the tapes of a canceled project his friend Alex had directed, and he had participated in, he discovers that his friends have been stalked by a paranormal entity known as the Operator and has now gotten himself involved in a mystery that goes beyond anything he can understand.::Alex Chapin / Anonymous
